&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>There are dozens of AI companies offering cloud-based AI solutions, and prices have been steadily decreasing over time. These models generally produce high-quality results because they are built with billions or even trillions of parameters and are hosted on world-class infrastructure. Given these advantages, why should we consider offline AI models? In this article, we explore the reasons behind this choice.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>